    {
      "id": "thermodynamics_statistical-entropy",
      "name": "Statistical Entropy (Boltzmann)",
      "description": "Statistical mechanics defines entropy by counting microstates: for an isolated system the multiplicity of microstates consistent with the macrostate gives Boltzmann's S = k ln(Omega); maximizing entropy subject to constraints selects the most probable macrostate, defines temperature through 1/T = dS/dE, and yields the second law dS >= 0.",
